The paper presents a semi-index based on q-grams, which is a common technique in information retrieval and database systems. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses space-time tradeoffs, which are relevant to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on datasets, which could also be relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
